NAME
    nix - nano-style text editor for Winix

SYNOPSIS
    nix [FILE]

DESCRIPTION
    nix is a simple, keyboard-driven text editor for the Winix shell
    environment. It follows a nano-style layout: a title bar at the top
    of the screen, the file contents in the middle, and a status/command
    bar at the bottom.

    Files are saved with Unix line endings (\n). Carriage returns (\r)
    are stripped on load. If FILE does not exist, a new empty file is
    opened.

    nix supports syntax highlighting for C/C++, Shell scripts, Python,
    and JSON when the file extension is recognized (.c, .cpp, .h, .sh,
    .py, .json).

    The undo history holds up to 512 operations and covers all edit
    types: character insertion, deletion, line splitting, line joining,
    tab insertion, cut, paste, and replace.

SCREEN LAYOUT
    Row 0        Title bar (filename, modified indicator) — inverse video
    Rows 1..R-2  File content with cursor
    Row R-1      Status bar / prompt area — inverse video

KEY BINDINGS
    Navigation:
      Arrow keys          Move cursor one character/line
      Home / Ctrl+A       Move to start of line
      End  / Ctrl+E       Move to end of line
      Page Up             Scroll one page up
      Page Down           Scroll one page down
      Ctrl+G              Go to a specific line number (prompts)

    Editing:
      Enter               Split line at cursor
      Backspace           Delete character to the left; join with
                          previous line when at column 0
      Delete              Delete character under cursor; join with next
                          line when at end of line
      Tab                 Insert 4 spaces
      Ctrl+K              Cut current line; repeat to accumulate
                          multiple lines into the clipboard
      Ctrl+U              Paste all cut lines above the cursor
      Ctrl+Z              Undo last operation

    Search and Replace:
      Ctrl+W              Find — prompt for search pattern
      Ctrl+N              Find next — repeat last search without prompt
      Ctrl+R              Find and replace — prompts for pattern and
                          replacement; interactive y/n/a/ESC loop
                          (y=replace this, n=skip, a=replace all,
                          ESC=cancel)

    File Operations:
      Ctrl+S              Save file (overwrites current file)
      Ctrl+X              Save and quit
      Ctrl+Q              Quit (prompts to save if modified)
      Ctrl+C              Force quit without saving

EXAMPLES
    nix README.txt
        Open README.txt for editing.

    nix newfile.py
        Create and edit a new Python file (syntax highlighting active).

    nix src/main.c
        Edit a C source file with C syntax highlighting.

EXIT STATUS
    0   Normal exit (file saved or no changes).
    1   Error (e.g., file could not be written).
